content:
My four year old is happy to try each level over and over until she gets 
the answer. The lessons are great for critical thinking.

Ok... So after receiving the reply from the devs about being "incorrect" 
about the fact that the paid version is exactly the same as the free one, 
it turns out that I was not incorrect. Apparently, there was a "glitch" in 
the free version I got, which had 6 castles in both the hard & the easy 
versions. Just wish the paid version had more. Love the game.
replyContent: Hi Laura, what you describe about the two versions is not true. The premium version offers all 12 castles (6 Easy & 6 Hard). In the freemium you can only play the first 4 (2 Easy & 2 Hard). If you were able to play all 12 castles in the free version, you either paid for the in-app purchase or else there must have been some kind of glitch.

content: My 4 year old and 6 year old are loving this game.
Likely the best app i've ever bought, kids love it!
Love this game and my kids too

My 5yo loves this game. The graphics are nice and gameplay is smooth. It is easily learned with a good learning curve. Kids will be challenged enough to stimulate their problem solving skills but there are enough design cues to help them work through when they get stuck. Nothing like seeing a 5yo absolutely frustrated that she can't get past a level but just refuses to give up until she solves it! I had an issue with installation of this game (user error) but the developers quickly helped me sort it out.
replyContent: Thanks so much for taking the time to share your feedback Channy! We are so glad to hear that your daughter loves Thinkrolls Kings & Queens and that she is so challenged and determined to solve the puzzles! :-)

content: When is the new thinkrolls coming out.....please reply!
replyContent: Thank you so much for playing our apps! :-) We are really happy you enjoy our Thinkrolls series! We can't really say when the next Thinkrolls will be out, but make sure you check out our website for our latest news. (www.avokiddo.com)

content: I really do love the game, it's fun for me and my child.  I bought the full version and am happy to have supported it.
replyContent: Hi Ann, the paid version offers all 12 castles (6 Easy & 6 Hard), while the free offers only 4 (2 & 2). For the castles to be playable, all previous ones must be completed, because kids need to master certain skills before advancing to more complex puzzles. So, some castles are disabled because you are yet to complete the previous ones.
